{"word":"εὐμαθής","slug":"εὐμαθής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐμαθής</b></el> <el>(εὐ-μᾰθής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:μανθάνω'><el>μανθάνω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>ready</i> or <i>quick at learning</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>docilis</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-θῶς</el>, <b><a href='S:Aeschines'>Aeschin.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>easy to learn</i> or <i>discern, intelligible</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>: <i>well-known</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}